definitions.definition: Any member of the genus Styrax of about 130 species of large shrubs or small trees, mostly native to temperate or tropical regions of the Northern Hemisphere .
The resin of the oriental sweetgum tree ( Liquidambar orientalis ), formerly used as a stimulating expectorant .
